subSubSection.paragraph:
Food and Feeding.
Cabrera’s Vole eats vegetation, only occasionally insects. Staple diet is leaves, stems, and seeds of monocotyledonous plants, in particular grasses (
Poaceae
), sedges (
Cyperaceae
), rushes (
Juncaceae
), and lilies (
Liliaceae
). It is selective, preferring some plants (e.g. brome) and avoiding others (e.g. false yellowhead). Clippings of vegetation are commonly found on runways.
